  "texts": [
    "CHRF CHRF (Popović, 2015) computes the Fscore of character-level N-gram matches.",
    "(1 + β 2)P R β 2 P + R, here β is a weight factor usually set to 1.",
    "CHRF is more robust to evaluate machine-generated texts of morphologically rich languages.",
    "However, CHRF is a surface metric that ignores the contextualized semantics between the candidate and reference text.",
    "Valid candidate AD like \"A person wearing a crimson jacket crosses the road.\""
  ],
